title: Looking for any lowgrade t204 commons I can find...
author: shammus

posts.post_title: Looking for any lowgrade t204 commons I can find...
posts.post_content:
Recently started collecting this set again.  Am looking to acquire as many commons as possible and I'd pay generously for a group of them.  Prefer lowgrade for the time being.  Have quite a bit of trade material too listed below.  Thanks in advance!
Brian
[url]redmaccie@hotmail.com[/url]

Larger groups available 
1909 Obak Group of 50 (would trade cards individually from this group)
w553 Group of 10 including Gehrig
z18 Group of 11 
R308s group of 45 w/ undeveloped cards and wrappers
1919 Zeenut NEAR-SET of 142/144 - most in the FR/GD range....very few catostrophic cards 
Individual Cards
d311 Wolverton GD/VG - one corner wrinkle....little wear otherwise 
d311 Tiedeman GD - staining on edges but no wear or wrinkling 
t212-1 Brown SGC 70 (horizontal) - only approx. 10-12 1909 Obaks graded higher!! 
t212-2 Ort SGC 10 "150 Series" - creasing on front 
t212-2 Stewart SGC 10 "150 Series" 
t222 Lee Magee SGC 10 - second toughest card in set 
e102 Wagner (fielding) SGC 10 - creases/corner wear. VERY RARE variation....exceedingly difficult!! 
1912 Zeenut Baker (horizontal) PSA 2 - two tiny corner creases...awesome pose and VERY difficult! 
v61 Neilsons Type 2 Woodall SGC 80 - gorgeous card!! 
w502 roush VG - blank back...sharp corners, one corner wrinkle 
w516-2-2 Grover Alexander SGC A - tougher variant of Alexander w/ caption at top and "Chicago" spelled backwards on his Jersey.  Neat card!  
w517 mini Cochrane VG - Mild residue on reverse and small wrinkle on front 
w517 mini Donahue EXMT - tougher blue variation!! Sharp corners, no wear or wrinkling 
w517 mini Kamm EXMT - Gorgeous card, no wear or wrinkling 
w517 mini Shires VG+ - This card I believe is actually cut from a 4 in 1 Exhibits postcard. However it's extremely scarce also and in a bright red variation 
w517 mini Waner EXMT - Gorgeous card...no wear or wrinkling and a tough red variation! 
w553 Cochrane VG/EX - No wear or wrinkling at all. Corners and edges are mostly sharp. Pinkish tint is harder to come by on this attractive set.  
F-50 1928 Harringtons Uhle GD - wrinkle across middle 
F-50 1928 Harringtons Bill Terry VG - mostly sharp corners, no wrinkling...mild stain in corner 
H-UNC 1911 Stevens Firearms Frank Baker (pink) PR - blotted with marker on front 
H-UNC 1928 Star Player Candy Charles Root SGC A - EXMT on front....sharp corners, great centering...no wear or wrinkling.  Staining on reverse 
r308 Tattoo Orbit Dykes - GD (staining) 
R-UNC 1936 Candy Card Pep Young VG/EX - No wear, wrinkling and corners/edges are mostly sharp.
